Package cs3500.easyanimator.model.actions

Class ASynchronisedActionSet

java.lang.Object
cs3500.easyanimator.model.actions.ASynchronisedActionSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
ISynchronisedActionSet, java.lang.Comparable<ISynchronisedActionSet>
Direct Known Subclasses:
SynchronizedActionSetImpl
public abstract class ASynchronisedActionSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISynchronisedActionSet
Represents an abstract implementation of a synchronized action. A synchronized action is a list of actions on a given shape that all share the same tick. Implements ISynchronisedActionSet. The simplest form of an action is an empty list of commands and a given amount of time.

  • Constructor Details

    • ASynchronisedActionSet

      public ASynchronisedActionSet​(int start, int end, java.util.List<IActionCommand> command)
      Constructor to create an instance of a singular shapes ISynchronisedActionSet. Can be abstracted to be applied to more than one shape in the future.
      Parameters:
      start - the start time of the animation
      end - the end time of the shapes animation
      command - the command to be applied to this shape for the given amount of time.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the commands are null
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - ticks are less than 0
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if starting tick is greater han or equal to ending tick
